@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
1. Introduction:

    Thankyou for taking an interest in TrUserEd - a fully GUI controlled user
editor for the @{"TransAmiga BBS" link "TA" 0} software.  TrUserEd allows the sysop to quickly
and easily load, edit and verify users even while a user is online. TrUserEd
allows you to interrogate and change an online user's settings, and has a
unique "preset" system to change a range of access settings in one simple
process.

@endnode

@node "Licence" "Licence"
2. Licence conditions:

    TrUserEd is another BistroWare (TM) product that comes with our unique
BistroWare registration conditions.  In it's unregistered form, TrUserEd,
like all other BistroWare (TM) products, distributed as "FreeWare", meaning
that you may use it as much as you like and as long as you like for absolutely
no charge or obligation whatsoever.

    There are, however, certain limitations in the unregistered version. In
unregistered form, TrUserEd will only recognise two different "preset" user
profiles.  When fully registered, the program will allow unlimited preset
user profiles.

    Secondly, the unregistered version will only recognise two TransAmiga
lines (TRANSAMIGA.0 and TRANSAMIGA.1) for the purposes of loading online user
data.  The registered version will look for the existence of all
TRANSAMIGA.<n> ports.

    If you like the program enough to want to register, see the section
headed "@{"registration" link "Registration" 0}" near the end of this document.

    As an added bonus, all BistroWare products require the same keyfile, so
PAY FOR ONE - GET THEM ALL!

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
3. Installation:

    Installation is quick and easy.  Just copy the TrUserEd drawer and all
it's contents to any handy spot on your hard (or floppy) disk/s. Double-click
on the TrUserEd icon to start the program.  TrUserEd only requires one config
setting, that of the path to locate NewUsers.BBS.  The system path is saved
as the first tooltype in TrUserEd.info.  Even if you neglect to add the path,
TrUserEd will prompt you when required and save the path to the icon file
anyway, so you hardly need to bother with it right away! ;-)

@endnode

@node "Use" "Using TrUserEd"
4. Using TrUserEd:

    When starting TrUserEd, you will be presented with a window containing all
the relevent user information.  Initially, all the details will be empty, as
you have not yet loaded any information!

    If you are not sure about what any of the feilds designate, then please
consult your TransAmiga documentation.

    A description of each of the menu item functions follows:

    a) The Program Menu contains three items.

        i) Verify New Users:

            Choose this item to verify all users who have completed the
        'join' proceedure in TransAmiga, but have not yet been verified
        by the sysop.  <Left Amiga>+<V> will also activate this function.

            On choosing this item, the first user not yet verified will be
        loaded into the editor for checking.  You are then free to make
        appropriate changes (if any) including applying any preset
        profiles, or you can delete the user or do nothing.  Select the
        same menu item again to load the next new user.  **NOTE that any
        changes made will not be saved unless you specifically choose to
        'Save' the changes!
    
        ii) About:

            This item displays a requestor box presenting some information
        about the program, version number and registration details.
        
        iii) Quit:

            Quits TrUserEd - of course! ;-)

    b) The User Menu contains a further four items:

        i) Load:

            This item will present you with a file requester listing the
        contents of your bbs:users directory.  Choose the name of the user
        you wish to edit, or their alias.  Clicking OK will present the
        user details.

        ii) Get Online User:

            This item will initially present a requester listing all active
        TransAmiga lines.  Click on the one you wish to load the details of
        the online user.  If there is no user currently online, you will be
        informed this.

        iii) Save:

            This item will save the user's details to the userfile. In the
        case of an online user, changes will become active as soon as you
        enter the new details in the user editor window.

        iv) Delete:

            This item will remove the currently loaded user from disk, as
        well as their @alias file if present.  If you change you mind after
        the event, don't worry, the user data is not lost from the editor.
        Just 'Save' the user back to disk again!

    c) The Presets Menu has just two items:

        i) Apply:

            Choose this item to apply a previously defined user profile to
        the user currently loaded.  You will be presented with a list of
        previously defined user profiles.  Click on the profile you wish to
        apply, and the currently loaded user data will be changed
        accordingly.  **Note that these changes will not take effect until
        you 'Save' the user data.

        ii) Create:

            This option will bring up the Preset User Profile Editor
        Window.  Choose a name for the preset profile and the fill in the
        details that you wish to be associated with that user type.  Blank
        fields will be ignored when applied to an existing user's data
        file.

            The flag cycles in this window have three options.  Either
        blank, meaning that the particular flag will not be changed on
        application, zero (0) meaning that the flag will be unset (set to
        '-'), and one (1) to set that flag (set to 'x') when applied.

@endnode

@node "Bugs" "Known Bugs"
5. Known Bugs:

    a) I am still having a bit of trouble getting TransAmiga to listen to
it's arexx port when i want it to.  Any of you who have been keeping up to
date with mail in the TransAmiga FidoNet echo may have seen some discussion
about this.  Because of this problem, TrUserEd loads an online user's data
from disk, rather than from the active BBS variables, so if a user has made
some changes (eg up/downloaded files) the changes will not be evident in the
datafile until they have logged off.

    b) Be careful when trying to load an online user's data during the logon
proceedure.  The results can be unpredictable.


@endnode

